<section><div class="section-inner"><div class="section-label">Regulatory Landscape</div><h2 class="section-title">The Shifting EU Export Framework</h2><p class="section-desc">The EU is transitioning from permissive to authorized-only waste exports. Here's how we stay ahead.</p><div class="grid-2" style="margin-bottom:2rem"><div class="compliance-card"><div class="badge">May 2026</div><h3>DIWASS Launch</h3><p>Mandatory digital filing of all Annex VII documents. Paper retired. Our operations are fully digital-ready.</p><ul><li>Digital Annex VII filing capability</li><li>Real-time shipment tracking</li><li>Paperless documentation end-to-end</li></ul></div><div class="compliance-card"><div class="badge">Nov 2026</div><h3>Plastic Ban &amp; Approved List</h3><p>Total ban on plastic waste exports to non-OECD. Our B3040 classification keeps us clear.</p><ul><li>All materials coded B3040 (rubber), not 070213 (plastic)</li><li>Malaysia highly likely on EU Approved List</li><li>Technical data sheets emphasize rubber composition</li></ul></div></div><div class="grid-2"><div class="compliance-card"><div class="badge">May 2027</div><h3>Audit Deadline</h3><p>Exports only to facilities passing independent EU-standard environmental audit. We are preparing.</p><ul><li>Facility audit preparation underway</li><li>Environmental monitoring operational</li><li>Ready for independent assessment</li></ul></div><div class="compliance-card"><div class="badge">Critical</div><h3>The Coding Trap</h3><p>Materials using EWC 070213 face automatic export blocks from Nov 2026. We exclusively use B3040.</p><ul><li>Exclusive Basel B3040 coding</li><li>No plastic waste cross-contamination</li><li>Invoices emphasize unvulcanized rubber nature</li></ul></div></div></div></section>
